headline: 2 Outstanding Dividend King Stocks and 1 ETF to Buy for a Lifetime of Passive Income
summary: The truth is, no one knows if a company has what it takes to reward its investors with a lifetime of passive income.  American States Water (NYSE: AWR) and Illinois Tool Works (NYSE: ITW) are both Dividend Kings -- meaning they have paid and raised their dividends for at least 50 consecutive years -- a track record that showcases their ability to grow earnings and pass along growing profits to shareholders through dividends.  Meanwhile, the JPMorgan Nasdaq Equity Premium Income ETF (NASDAQ: JEPQ) is a unique, ultra-high-yield investment that uses financial instruments to generate income primarily from growth stocks.
